definitions.definition: An irrational need or irresistible urge to perform some action, often despite negative consequences.
examples: During the basketball game, I had a sudden compulsion to have a smoke .

definitions.definition: The use of authority , influence , or other power to force ( compel ) a person or persons to act.
The lawful use of violence (i.e. by the administration ).
